Oh, I thought they were in an Alleyway above ground.

Doggeds speed was concentrated on the falling debris around him. &quot;This bots
crazy!&quot; he thought knowing such a reckless attack could easily bring the
entire tunnel down on them all. He noticed the second shot but didn&#39;t have
time to move as it collided with him sending him rolling back from the
impact. He reached up to feal his shoulder quickly learning that a gaping
hole was now where his plating had been. He tried to move his arm, pain
shooting through every servo in his body. His hand opened dropping his disk
launcher to the ground. He opened a link to the others, &quot;The preys biting
back.&quot; He shouts trying to hold back his pain. &quot;Do we really need the
supplies this badly?&quot; The Cybrats had normally taken whatever they needed
but now what Dogged needed was a medic.

Dogged fealt a mysterious wave of virtigo come over him. He thought that the
injuries were causing his mental state. He glanced in the direction of
Repugnus and quickly realized that it was the Monsterbot who was causing his
problems. He tried to recover his launcher when pain shit through his
injured arm. The smallest of the Cybrats was nothing more than a useless
target. In his condition ther was no way he&#39;d be of any use to his team.
